The paper discusses the vulnerability of deep learning models to adversarial examples and proposes a new type of neural network architecture to increase robustness in adversarial settings. This topic is closely related to several sub-categories of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), computer security and cryptography (cs.CR), computer vision and pattern recognition (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE). Therefore, these are the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper.
